# Malachar's Journal

on "read malachar journal" {
  require has_item(malachar_journal)
  effect set_flag(malachar_journal_read)
  effect add_score(5)
  success "The journal is written in a hand that grew increasingly erratic. Malachar was a wizard who believed the Founders hoarded magic that should belong to all. He tried to take the Convergence Stone by force. When the Founders defeated him, he cursed the Stone with his dying breath — a curse that would fester for a thousand years before striking. He wrote: 'If I cannot have it, I will ensure that one day, neither can they. The wards will fail. The Stone will corrupt. And Hogwarts will learn what it means to be unprotected.'"
  fail "You don't have Malachar's journal."
  done "You already know Malachar's story."
  once
}

# --- Puzzle 22: The Four Tokens ---

on "place token" in [convergence_antechamber] {
  require has_item(gryffindor_token)
  require has_item(ravenclaw_token)
  require has_item(hufflepuff_token)
  require has_item(slytherin_token)
  effect remove_item(gryffindor_token)
  effect remove_item(ravenclaw_token)
  effect remove_item(hufflepuff_token)
  effect remove_item(slytherin_token)
  effect set_flag(tokens_placed)
  effect reveal_exit(antechamber_convergence)
  effect solve_puzzle(token_placement)
  effect add_score(25)
  success "One by one, you place the Founder Tokens in their alcoves. Each slides home with a resonant click: gold sword, silver diadem, bronze cup, emerald locket. The four tokens blaze with light — and the rune-carved door at the south end of the antechamber shudders, cracks, and swings inward. Beyond it, you can feel the Convergence Stone calling."
  fail "You need all four Founder Tokens to proceed."
  done "The tokens are already placed."
  once
}

