# --- Puzzle 23: Sealing the Stone ---

# Path A: Unity Ending (best — requires all virtue flags)

on "cast unity charm" in [convergence_chamber] {
  require has_item(wand)
  require has_flag(ron_rescued)
  require has_flag(loyalty_proven)
  require has_flag(stranger_healed)
  require has_flag(draco_allied)
  effect set_flag(stone_sealed_unity)
  effect solve_puzzle(convergence_seal)
  effect add_score(35)
  success "You raise your wand. The four tokens — even from their alcoves — blaze with light: gold, blue, yellow, green. You feel them all: Ron's courage, Hermione's wisdom, the ghost's gratitude, Draco's grudging trust. 'UNITAS!' The word tears itself from your throat. The Convergence Stone sings — a clear, piercing note — and Malachar's curse shatters like black glass, its shards dissolving into nothing. The chamber fills with light so bright it burns your eyes, then fades to a warm, steady glow. The wards hum with renewed strength. It is done."
  fail "The Unity Charm requires the strength of all four virtues. You haven't earned them all."
  done "The Stone is already sealed."
  once
}

on "seal stone unity" in [convergence_chamber] {
  require has_item(wand)
  require has_flag(ron_rescued)
  require has_flag(loyalty_proven)
  require has_flag(stranger_healed)
  require has_flag(draco_allied)
  effect set_flag(stone_sealed_unity)
  effect solve_puzzle(convergence_seal)
  effect add_score(35)
  success "You raise your wand. The four tokens — even from their alcoves — blaze with light: gold, blue, yellow, green. You feel them all: Ron's courage, Hermione's wisdom, the ghost's gratitude, Draco's grudging trust. 'UNITAS!' The word tears itself from your throat. The Convergence Stone sings — a clear, piercing note — and Malachar's curse shatters like black glass, its shards dissolving into nothing. The chamber fills with light so bright it burns your eyes, then fades to a warm, steady glow. The wards hum with renewed strength. It is done."
  fail "The Unity Charm requires the strength of all four virtues. You haven't earned them all."
  done "The Stone is already sealed."
  once
}

# Path B: Sacrifice Ending

on "touch convergence stone" in [convergence_chamber] {
  require has_item(wand)
  effect set_flag(stone_sealed_sacrifice)
  effect solve_puzzle(convergence_seal)
  effect add_score(35)
  success "You step forward and press your hand against the Convergence Stone. It is cold — impossibly cold — and then it is not. Heat floods through your palm, up your arm, into your chest. Everything you are — every spell, every instinct, every spark of magic you have ever felt — pours out of you and into the crystal. The curse screams. Then it stops. The Stone pulses with clean, steady light. The wards reform. But when you pull your hand away, your fingers feel numb. Something inside you has gone quiet. The magic is gone. Hogwarts is saved."
  fail "You need your wand to channel the magic."
  done "The Stone is already sealed."
  once
}

on "seal stone sacrifice" in [convergence_chamber] {
  require has_item(wand)
  effect set_flag(stone_sealed_sacrifice)
  effect solve_puzzle(convergence_seal)
  effect add_score(35)
  success "You step forward and press your hand against the Convergence Stone. It is cold — impossibly cold — and then it is not. Heat floods through your palm, up your arm, into your chest. Everything you are — every spell, every instinct, every spark of magic you have ever felt — pours out of you and into the crystal. The curse screams. Then it stops. The Stone pulses with clean, steady light. The wards reform. But when you pull your hand away, your fingers feel numb. Something inside you has gone quiet. The magic is gone. Hogwarts is saved."
  fail "You need your wand to channel the magic."
  done "The Stone is already sealed."
  once
}

# Path C: Rival's Redemption (Draco allied but not full unity)

on "seal stone together" in [convergence_chamber] {
  require has_item(wand)
  require has_flag(draco_allied)
  effect set_flag(stone_sealed_rival)
  effect solve_puzzle(convergence_seal)
  effect add_score(35)
  success "'Together, Potter. On three.' Draco steps up beside you, wand drawn. You have never cast a spell in tandem with Draco Malfoy. His magic is precise where yours is forceful. The combined stream hits the Stone and the curse buckles, retreating into the deepest layers of the crystal. 'It'll hold,' Draco says, breathing hard. 'But someone will need to reinforce the seal. Regularly.' He almost smiles. Almost."
  fail "You need Draco's cooperation for this approach."
  done "The Stone is already sealed."
  once
}

on "cast seal with draco" in [convergence_chamber] {
  require has_item(wand)
  require has_flag(draco_allied)
  effect set_flag(stone_sealed_rival)
  effect solve_puzzle(convergence_seal)
  effect add_score(35)
  success "'Together, Potter. On three.' Draco steps up beside you, wand drawn. You have never cast a spell in tandem with Draco Malfoy. His magic is precise where yours is forceful. The combined stream hits the Stone and the curse buckles, retreating into the deepest layers of the crystal. 'It'll hold,' Draco says, breathing hard. 'But someone will need to reinforce the seal. Regularly.' He almost smiles. Almost."
  fail "You need Draco's cooperation for this approach."
  done "The Stone is already sealed."
  once
}

# Path D: Partial Seal (default)

on "seal stone" in [convergence_chamber] {
  require has_item(wand)
  effect set_flag(stone_sealed_partial)
  effect solve_puzzle(convergence_seal)
  effect add_score(35)
  success "You raise your wand and cast the sealing charm alone. Magic flows from you into the Stone — but not enough. The curse retreats but does not break. The Stone's light is dimmer than it should be, flickering at the edges. You can feel the seal settling into place, imperfect but holding. It will last years. Perhaps decades. But not forever."
  fail "You need your wand to seal the Stone."
  done "The Stone is already sealed."
  once
}

on "cast seal" in [convergence_chamber] {
  require has_item(wand)
  effect set_flag(stone_sealed_partial)
  effect solve_puzzle(convergence_seal)
